>
>  Ah, beg to differ here, but I think you have it backwards
> here. Optically-triggered systems are fine unless the light source gets
> dusty, dirty, oily or grimy - then the beam of light is affected negatively.
> Hall-effect magnetic systems, on the other hand, are not affected by dust,
> dirt, oil, grime and moisture.
